{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 01:40:54.743625", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Anomaly detected**\\n\\nAll ping tests between the hosts on the 10.0.0.0/24 subnet fail:\\n\\n| Source → Destination | Result |\\n|----------------------|--------|\\n| host_1_1 → host_1_2 | 100\\u202f% packet loss |\\n| host_1_1 → host_2_1 | 100\\u202f% packet loss |\\n| leaf_1 → host_1_1   | Network is unreachable |\\n\\n**Faulty device(s)**\\n\\n* **leaf_1** – the leaf switch that should be bridging the hosts.\\n\\n**Root cause**\\n\\n`leaf_1` is not configured to bridge the 10.0.0.0/24 network:\\n\\n* The only IP address on `leaf_1` is on `eth6` (20.0.0.3/24).  \\n* No interface on `leaf_1` has an address in the 10.0.0.0/24 subnet.  \\n* The OVS system (`ovs-system`) is present but no bridge is created or attached to the host ports.  \\n* Consequently, packets from `host_1_1` and `host_1_2` never reach each other, and the hosts cannot reach the switch itself.\\n\\n**Summary**\\n\\nThe leaf switch is mis‑configured (missing bridge/VLAN for the 10.0.0.0/24 subnet), which prevents any traffic between the hosts on that subnet. Fixing the switch configuration (creating a bridge, assigning the correct VLAN, and ensuring the switch ports are in the same bridge) will restore connectivity., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='6ea7ad25-d13a-419f-8c7d-fbb97ba9c6c2'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
